message.content:
cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on remote attestation, a crucial security service for IoT and embedded devices. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper presents a new design and implementation of control-flow attestation for embedded systems software. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach using a real-world embedded (cyber-physical) application. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of TrustZone hardware security extensions and the implementation of the proposed approach on Raspberry Pi. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper utilizes ARM TrustZone hardware security extensions for the implementation of the proposed approach.
